Week 1: Cryptography Fundamentals & Security Awareness
Focus: What cryptography is + why it’s critical in cybersecurity

Days 1–2
Read basic cryptography concepts
What is cryptography?
Definition and goals of cryptography
Cryptography vs encoding vs hashing
Why cryptography is essential in cybersecurity

Try Cryptography Basics in TryHackMe to apply terms like plaintext/ciphertext and simple ciphers

Days 3–4
Types of cryptography:
Symmetric encryption (shared key)
Asymmetric encryption (public/private key)
Hash functions

Do hands-on exercises in TryHackMe (hashing and simple symmetric/asymmetric examples)
Optionally view HTTPS/TLS modules in PortSwigger Academy to relate cryptography → real web security

Days 5–6
Common cryptographic algorithms (high level):
Symmetric: AES, DES (why DES is broken)
Asymmetric: RSA, ECC
Hashing: SHA-256, MD5 (why MD5 is insecure)

Complete Breaking Crypto the Simple Way to practice weak crypto cases and key brute-forcing
Try additional rooms like Crack the Hash for practical hash cracking

